We might also add attributes and functionality in the base classes in the future if this makes sense.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
This is a placeholder for technical information needed during the execution of operational rules.
RuleResult contains technical information about the success or failure when applying a rule on a certain object. Typical information includes which elements were created, which elements could be matched, which elements could not be matched and are thus untranslated so far.
Such information is used by the translation algorithm to control the rule application.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
Basic super class for all correspondence link types.
Every correspondence link type inherits from this class. Nevertheless, since any metamodel can be used to be correspondence model, this inheritance will be added automatically by our compiling engine.
This type is the central point to introduce new functionality to the correspondence domain.
